---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { Icon } from 'astro-icon/components';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Volunteer | MCM Amateur Radio Operations"
  description="Volunteer registration for MCM Amateur Radio Operators opens around June 1. Register through the Marine Corps Marathon volunteer system, then access the Amateur Radio Operator portal."
>
  <div class="py-12 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <Icon name="lucide:user-plus" class="w-16 h-16 mx-auto text-[#CC0000] mb-4" aria-hidden="true" />
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Volunteer Registration</h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          Registration opens on or about June 1 each year through the Marine Corps Marathon volunteer system. Use the
          information below to register and access the Amateur Radio Operator portal.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-sm p-8 mb-8">
        <div class="space-y-5 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            Volunteer registration for Amateur Radio Operators supporting the Marine Corps Marathon typically opens on or
            about June 1 each year. Operators interested in supporting the race should monitor the official Marine Corps
            Marathon volunteer page for registration announcements and updates:
          </p>
          <p>
            <a
              href="https://www.marinemarathon.com/volunteer"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="font-semibold text-[#CC0000] underline hover:text-[#A00000]"
              >Marine Corps Marathon Volunteer Page</a
            >
          </p>
          <p>
            Once volunteer registration opens, operators must first complete registration through the Marine Corps
            Marathon volunteer system. After registering, you should receive an email within approximately one week with
            instructions for accessing the Amateur Radio Operator portal.
          </p>
          <p>
            After logging into the site, operators will have access to important event information and documents,
            including:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 marker:text-[#CC0000]">
            <li>Operator guides</li>
            <li>Frequency plans</li>
            <li>Assignment information</li>
            <li>Communications and event updates</li>
            <li>Training and operational materials</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            The Amateur Radio team plays a critical role in supporting race operations, medical coordination, logistics,
            and runner safety throughout the event. We appreciate your willingness to volunteer and support the Marine
            Corps Marathon.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-sm p-6 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Why Volunteer?</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-700">
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <Icon name="lucide:radio" class="w-5 h-5 text-[#CC0000] shrink-0 mt-0.5" aria-hidden="true" />
            <span>Participate in one of the nation's most prestigious marathon events</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <Icon name="lucide:radio" class="w-5 h-5 text-[#CC0000] shrink-0 mt-0.5" aria-hidden="true" />
            <span>Gain experience in large-scale emergency communications and event support</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <Icon name="lucide:radio" class="w-5 h-5 text-[#CC0000] shrink-0 mt-0.5" aria-hidden="true" />
            <span>Network with fellow amateur radio operators from across the region</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <Icon name="lucide:radio" class="w-5 h-5 text-[#CC0000] shrink-0 mt-0.5" aria-hidden="true" />
            <span>Contribute to runner safety and race success</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
